This paper focuses on natural language processing tasks such as machine comprehension, answer selection, and text entailment, which are typically categorized under cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) for aggregation, which is a popular technique in the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper explores different comparison functions for matching two vectors, which is relevant to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper uses datasets that involve text, which could also be relevant to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision) where text recognition is a common task.
